entry.title: Ron Miles (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Ron Miles (pictured), who would have turned 59 today, played in the same high school jazz band as Don Cheadle?

entry.title: attack on the Delhi chief minister's residence (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that during the attack on the Delhi chief minister's residence, protesters painted the gate red and tried to scale it while police officers watched?

entry.title: Francis Orray Ticknor (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Francis Orray Ticknor was a country doctor whose fame as a poet relies on "Little Giffen", a poem about one of his patients who died in the American Civil War?

entry.title: Du, o schönes Weltgebäude (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the 1653 hymn "Du, o schönes Weltgebäude", about renouncing the world, contains the stanza "Komm, O Tod, du Schlafes Bruder", which Bach used to conclude his cross-staff cantata?

entry.title: Satyagraha Hoerip (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Satyagraha Hoerip wrote a short story set during the Indonesian mass killings of 1965–66 from the perspective of the killers-to-be?

entry.title: NBA Comeback Player of the Year Award (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the NBA Comeback Player of the Year Award was canceled, reportedly because of drugs?

entry.title: call to prayer (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a call to prayer is a common feature to Christianity, Islam and Judaism?

entry.title: Recess Therapy (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that topics on Recess Therapy have included the economy, climate change, and peeing your pants?
